<DocLayout title="Acceptable Use Policy" description="Acceptable use policy governing automated access, content use, compliance claims, and system integrity for AEGIS Initiative websites.">
  <h1>Acceptable Use Policy</h1>

  <p><em>Effective: March 21, 2026</em></p>

  <p>
    This Acceptable Use Policy (&ldquo;AUP&rdquo;) governs your use of AEGIS Initiative websites and all related
    AEGIS&trade; materials. This AUP supplements the <a href="/legal/terms/">Terms of Use</a> &mdash; violations of this
    policy may result in enforcement actions described therein.
  </p>

  <hr />

  <h2>Automated Access</h2>

  <p>
    Automated access to the Services is permitted only within the bounds of the site&rsquo;s <code>robots.txt</code>
    file. The following are prohibited without prior written permission:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>
      Scraping, crawling, or systematically downloading site content beyond what <code>robots.txt</code> allows
    </li>
    <li>Using bots, spiders, or automated tools to index, mirror, or reproduce site content</li>
    <li>Circumventing rate limits, access controls, or technical restrictions</li>
  </ul>

  <hr />

  <h2>Content Use Restrictions</h2>

  <p>
    The AEGIS Constitution is licensed under the <a href="/legal/#license">Apache License 2.0</a>. Within that license,
    the following restrictions apply:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>No misrepresentation.</strong> You may not present AEGIS&trade; content as your own original work, remove
      attribution, or alter content in ways that misrepresent the AEGIS Initiative&rsquo;s positions.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>No unauthorized redistribution.</strong> Redistribution must comply with Apache 2.0 requirements &mdash;
      including retention of copyright notices, license text, and clear marking of modifications.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>No AI training use without permission.</strong> Use of AEGIS&trade; content as training data for machine
      learning models, large language models, or other AI systems requires explicit written permission from Finnoybu IP
      LLC. To request permission, contact
      <a href="mailto:legal@aegis-initiative.com">legal@aegis-initiative.com</a>.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <p>For trademark restrictions, see <a href="/legal/">Copyright, Trademark &amp; License</a>.</p>

  <hr />

  <h2>AEGIS Compliance Claims</h2>

  <p>You may not:</p>

  <ul>
    <li>
      Claim that a system, product, or service is &ldquo;AEGIS-compliant&rdquo; or &ldquo;AEGIS-certified&rdquo;
      without meeting the requirements defined in the AEGIS Constitution
    </li>
    <li>
      Use AEGIS&trade; marks to imply endorsement or affiliation with the AEGIS Initiative without written permission
    </li>
    <li>Represent unofficial implementations as authoritative AEGIS governance systems</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    Stating compatibility (<em>&ldquo;Compatible with AEGIS&trade; specifications&rdquo;</em>) is permitted as described
    in the <a href="/legal/#permitted-uses">trademark policy</a>.
  </p>

  <hr />

  <h2>System Integrity</h2>

  <p>You may not:</p>

  <ul>
    <li>
      Attempt to probe, scan, or test the vulnerability of the Services or their infrastructure without authorization
    </li>
    <li>
      Attempt to gain unauthorized access to any portion of the Services, their servers, or connected systems
    </li>
    <li>
      Interfere with or disrupt the Services&rsquo; availability, including denial-of-service attacks or deliberate
      overloading
    </li>
    <li>Introduce malicious code, viruses, or other harmful material</li>
  </ul>

  <hr />

  <h2>Reporting Violations</h2>

  <p>
    To report a violation of this policy, contact
    <a href="mailto:legal@aegis-initiative.com">legal@aegis-initiative.com</a> or see
    <a href="/legal/impressum/#contact">Impressum</a> for additional contact options.
  </p>

  <hr />

  <h2>Enforcement</h2>

  <p>Violations of this AUP may result in:</p>

  <ul>
    <li>Warning and request to cease the prohibited activity</li>
    <li>Temporary or permanent restriction of access to the Services</li>
    <li>Termination of any license or permission granted under these policies</li>
    <li>Legal action as appropriate</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    AEGIS Operations LLC reserves the right to take enforcement action at its sole discretion. For the full terms
    governing enforcement, termination, and dispute resolution, see <a href="/legal/terms/">Terms of Use</a>.
  </p>

